Bring every person (parents, therapists, teachers, older siblings) who will be involved in replacing the maladaptive behavior. It is best if everyone meets at the same time and place so that no misunderstandings can exist. One team member should take notes or record the meeting. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b6/Extinguish-Maladaptive-Behavior-in-Children-with-Disabilities-Step-2.jpg/v4-460px-Extinguish-Maladaptive-Behavior-in-Children-with-Disabilities-Step-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b6/Extinguish-Maladaptive-Behavior-in-Children-with-Disabilities-Step-2.jpg/v4-760px-Extinguish-Maladaptive-Behavior-in-Children-with-Disabilities-Step-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Describe and define the target behavior so that there is no confusion as to exactly what the problem is. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0e/Extinguish-Maladaptive-Behavior-in-Children-with-Disabilities-Step-3.jpg/v4-460px-Extinguish-Maladaptive-Behavior-in-Children-with-Disabilities-Step-3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0e/Extinguish-Maladaptive-Behavior-in-Children-with-Disabilities-Step-3.jpg/v4-760px-Extinguish-Maladaptive-Behavior-in-Children-with-Disabilities-Step-3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
